$f(t)$ can be divided to to stages;
* exponential growth function $(t \leq \mathrm{argmax}\ \Delta C(t))$ and
* negative exponential function $(otherwise)$.

With constant $(a, b, A, B, C)$,
$$
f(t) = \left\{
\begin{array}{ll}
    a e^{bt} & (t \leq \mathrm{argmax}\ \Delta C(t)) \\
    C - Ae^{-Bt} & (otherwise)
\end{array}
\right.
$$

